# Files EAS Build should NOT upload when building the mobile (Expo) app.
# Uses .gitignore syntax. This lives at the repo root because EAS archives the
# whole git repository for the build.
#
# The Expo app in mobile/ is self-contained and does not depend on the Laravel
# backend. Excluding the backend also avoids a Windows symlink
# (backend/public/storage) that breaks the EAS upload, and keeps the archive small.

/backend

# Report / documentation artifacts and build scripts — not needed for the app.
/docs
*.docx
*.pptx
*.py
~$*
GeoTrack_*
Post-Data-Slide*
